[Predictions]

@fentymix i agree with that logic but i actually think his cardio will still be bad simply because Estevam has poor energy management. In the Aguilar/InnerG fights he was shooting nonstop and immediately moving with his opponent whenever they tried to get up. Aguilar was able to repeatedly get up and instead of trying to take the back or slow things down, Estevam kept overexerting on takedowns and gassed himself out badly; that’s the only fight in the ufc he’s made weight for as well, and was the fight he death gassed the hardest. He looked fine last fight but in that fight he was also allowed free top control since Bunes is a guard player with no tdd. I think moving up is actually a really bad move in terms of Estevam’s style translating. Outside of Bunes he was not controlling either guy for very long periods of time. They couldn’t stop the transitions or successive takedowns, but they were able to get to their feet and separate on multiple occasions. Now you have to factor in that Estevam is now going up against guys the same size/bigger than him, meaning he will have to use even more energy than he already did with his style. I think this and his poor cardio management (as well as carrying extra weight, since this is a permanent move) are actually going to be a real problem.

Ewing also fights at a very high pace in every single fight and his entire style is constant forward pressure; literally every fight of his he puts his opponents on the backfoot right away and starts swinging. Estevam obviously can’t hang on the feet here anyways, but we’ve also seen he absolutely hates getting put on the backfoot. Ewing has more power than guys he’s fought before, as well as a speed advantage here. A lot of people are harping on him for the Brand fight but if you watch literally any of his other fights Ewing actually showed very good defensive grappling. He did lose his debut via wrestling to Edwin Cooper, but that was at 145 against a D1 all American. I don’t think Ewings’s tdd is perfect but his scrambles/get ups/defensive grappling are much better than what he showed in the Brand fight

